    "assumptions": [
      "Scope is narrow: relax the CachedWinnerFirstDecision validator to accept cacheVersion 2 AND the decisionState value 'refusal', plus ship a migration script. No write-path changes. No consumer rewires. No type removals. PR #2 handles those.",
      "Migration walks every transcript with a non-null summaryCache. For each row: compute canonical from the existing decisionCode + pair + orientationFlipped, write cacheVersion 2, map 'refusal' decisionCode to decisionState='refusal', strip decisionCode/decisionCodeSource from the cache. Per-row atomic UPDATE; no global lock.",
      "orientationFlipped is read from scenarios.orientation_flipped (Boolean column). Value pair is read from transcripts.definition_snapshot.components.{value_first,value_second}.token. Malformed or missing snapshot: log and skip (reported in dry-run as 'missing-snapshot').",
      "Refusal detection: a row with decisionCode='refusal' in cache maps to decisionState='refusal', strength='unknown', favoredValueKey=null. Rows with no decisionCode in cache but cacheVersion=1: preserve existing canonical values verbatim, only bump cacheVersion to 2. No retroactive refusal inference from legacy data.",
      "Migration script is dry-run by default; --apply to write. Reports categorized counts in dry-run. Idempotent \u2014 safe to re-run. Python helper at cloud/scripts/reparse-decision-stdin.py already exists from PR #695 and can be reused.",
      "External API shape (MCP, CSV) unchanged in this PR. PR #2 breaks those contracts."
    ],
    "summary": "PR #1 of a larger refactor. Context carried over from the decision-cache-single-source spec \u2014 requirements are settled. No open questions.",
